<section class="guide">
  <h1>4. Configure Your Domain</h1>
  <p class="lead">Connect your custom domain to Cloudflare Pages with automatic SSL.</p>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  <p>Cloudflare DNS is nameserver-based. You update nameservers at your domain registrar to point to Cloudflare. No domain transfer needed.</p>

  <h2>Set Up DNS</h2>
  <p>Tell your assistant:</p>
  <blockquote>"Set up the domain yourdomain.com for this project."</blockquote>

  <p>Your assistant will:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create a Cloudflare DNS zone for your domain</li>
    <li>Give you two nameserver hostnames to set at your registrar</li>
    <li>Add CNAME records pointing to your Pages URL (with CNAME flattening for the root domain)</li>
    <li>Register the custom domain with your Cloudflare Pages project</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>DNS Records Created</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Value</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>yourdomain.com</td>
        <td>CNAME (flattened)</td>
        <td>project-slug.pages.dev</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>www.yourdomain.com</td>
        <td>CNAME</td>
        <td>project-slug.pages.dev</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>SSL Certificate</h2>
  <p>SSL provisions automatically once Cloudflare's nameservers are active. No manual setup needed.</p>

  <h2>DNS Propagation</h2>
  <p>Cloudflare DNS is near-instant once nameservers propagate at the registrar. This typically takes 5 minutes to a few hours.</p>

  <p>To test immediately:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the Pages URL (always works): <code>https://project-slug.pages.dev</code></li>
    <li>Check DNS propagation: <code>dig yourdomain.com @1.1.1.1</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Search Console Verification</h2>
  <p>Once your domain is live, verify it in Google Search Console:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create a GSC property for your domain</li>
    <li>Choose DNS verification and copy the TXT record value</li>
    <li>Tell your assistant: "Add GSC verification TXT record: google-site-verification=xxxx"</li>
    <li>Click "Verify" in GSC</li>
  </ol>

